fixing of function app code to point to a storage account

1️⃣ Add outputs to storageAccount.bicep

Scroll to the very end of the file (after the blobPrivateEndpoint resource that you showed) and add this outside any resource block:

// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Outputs – used by other modules (e.g. Function App)
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Storage account name
output storageAccountName string = storage.name

// Connection string for AzureWebJobsStorage, marked as secure
@secure()
output storageAccountConnectionString string = 'DefaultEndpointsProtocol=https;AccountName=${storage.name};AccountKey=${listKeys(storage.id, ''2022-09-01'').keys[0].value};EndpointSuffix=${environment().suffixes.storage}'


2️⃣ Quick reminder what happens next (you may already have started this)

In functionApp.bicep add parameters:

@secure()
param storageAccountConnectionString string
param storageAccountName string

…and in siteConfig.appSettings add:

{
  name: 'AzureWebJobsStorage'
  value: storageAccountConnectionString
}
{
  name: 'STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME'
  value: storageAccountName
}

In main.bicep, where you call the Function App module, pass the outputs:

module cdbToBridgeFunction '../../../../../bicep-modules/Bicep/modules/Compute/functionApp.bicep' = {
  name: 'deploy-cdb-bridge-function'
  params: {
    ...
    storageAccountConnectionString: storageAccount.outputs.storageAccountConnectionString
    storageAccountName: storageAccount.outputs.storageAccountName
    ...
  }
}
